ose what they are taught and how its done.... If you look everywhere on the documents written by our forefathers and mothers....our country and laws have a religious foundation, I don't care which religion it is in particular...actually yes I do care...no Islam......I don't mean to say that the bible ought to be read in schools either......though it wouldn't hurt anything, the government cant get anything right and I am not trusting them with my children. (I knew that my comments would p*ss off some ppl.) ....Look, you said I ruined it with religion....well...I am not such a religious church going person myself, but I want to let my children decide which way to go when they grow up.....they need to have that choice, they aren't going to get that in public schools. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1082" language="en" documentId="2413" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Nelson M" date="Aug 30, 2013 5:52AM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="9" thumbsDown="0" origId="2413" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1082"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>